`★ Insight ─────────────────────────────────────`
This component follows the "extract pure functions for testability" pattern documented in progress.md. The heavy layout math (`calculateButtonPositions`) and hit-testing logic (`isClickOutsideMenu`, `getNextFocusIndex`) are pure exported functions tested without any DOM or React rendering. The React component itself is a thin wiring layer that composes these functions with SVG rendering and keyboard/mouse event listeners. This is the same approach used for `ObjectSelectionSystem` — it avoids needing `@testing-library/react` or `jsdom` while still achieving high test coverage of the important logic.
